{"lemma":"عَصَبَ","slug":"عَصَبَ","root":"ع.ص.ب","root_slug":"ع-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29265"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to twist, wrap around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fold tightly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bound or bind, to tie"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to castrate via a band around testicles"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bandage"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw people together, to assemble"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to surround, to encompass"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to surround, to encompass; to include, to hold or reckon together, such as the entirety of one's relations, to be of the same identity"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obligate, to bind responsibility or consequences to; especially with phrases like بِ (bi) + رَأْس (raʔs, “head”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause a thing to be twisted, or wrapped around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swaddle, to cause a thing to be tightly folded around"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bandage, to tourniquet"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turban, to wrap one's brow with a band"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turban, to wrap one's brow with a band; to crown, to declare or cause one to be a chief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nerve"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sinew, tendon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"muscle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"band, ribbon, scarf"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chieftain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandees","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"somewhat distant relations","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bindweed (Convolvulus)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.sˤa.ba/","/ʕasˤ.sˤa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29265","headword_ar":"عَصَبَ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA:) this is the primary signification: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]; (A, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]: (A, Mgh, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing with another thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lengthwise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [more commonly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) See also 2, first sentence. [And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَعْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spun,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thread. (K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put together"},{"kind":"text","text":"thread,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"it, previously to dyeing it. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkabo$a","text_ar":"الكَبْشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, *] aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the testicles of the ram, in order that they might fall, without his extracting them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) and in like manner one says of a goat, (K,) and of other beasts. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K, *) aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtSbhA","text_ar":"اعتصبها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound the thighs of the she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lower parts of her nostrils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a cord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) in order that she might yield her milk copiously: (Msb, K, TA:) and (O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxi*a Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"فَخِذَ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound the thigh of the she-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for that purpose. (S, O.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSuwbN","text_ar":"عَصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTaY EalaY AlEaSobi","text_ar":"اَعْطَى عَلَى العَصْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave by means of force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivoliY laA yadir~u biAlEiSaAbi","text_ar":"مِثْلِى لَا يَدِرُّ بِالعِصَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one as I am will not give by means of force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabato farojahaA","text_ar":"عَصَبَتْ فَرْجَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound her vulva with a bandage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Al$~ajarapa","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الشَّجَرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew together the branches of the tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that were straggling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of a rope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then beat it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) in order that its leaves might fall. (S, O, TA.) [Golius assigns this signification also to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaS~aba","text_ar":"عَصَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as on the authority of the S, in which I do not find it.] El-Hajjáj said, (S, TA,) when preaching to the people at El-Koofeh, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aEoSiban~akumo","text_ar":"لَاَعْصِبَنَّكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSoba Als~alami","text_ar":"عَصْبَ السَّلَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alamapi","text_ar":"السَّلَمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly draw you together and beat you as one does the selem"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the selemeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamap","text_ar":"سَلَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tree of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":", having thorns, and its leaves are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with which hides are tanned: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZN","text_ar":"قَرَظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the removal of the leaves with the hand being difficult on account of the many thorns, its branches are drawn together and bound tightly with a rope; then the beater pulls them towards him, and beats them with his staff; whereupon the leaves become scattered for the cattle and for him who desires to gather them. (TA.) Or this is done, (S, O, TA,) accord. to A 'Obeyd, (S, O,) only (TA) when they desire to cut down the selemeh, that they may get at the stock. (S, O, TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA tuEoSabu salamaAtuhu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا تُعْصَبُ سَلَمَاتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not have his selemehs bound round with a rope, and beaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a prov., applied to a strong, mighty man, not to be subdued nor abased. (A, * TA.) And one says also of winds,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoSibu Al$~ajara Einoda duruwjihaA fiyhi","text_ar":"تَعْصِبُ الشَّجَرَ عِنْدَ دُرُوجِهَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They compress the branches of the trees, as though they bound them round, in their passage among them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and such winds are termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَصَايِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alqawoma","text_ar":"عَصَبَ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an affair, or event,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew the people together, and became severe to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba SadoEa AlzujaAjapi biDab~apK mino fiD~apK","text_ar":"عَصَبَ صَدْعَ الزُجَاجَةِ بِضَبَّةٍ مِنْ فِضَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a smith)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired the crack of the glass vessel by putting round it a band of silver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba biraA^osi qawomihi AlEaAra","text_ar":"عَصَبَ بِرَاْسِ قَوْمِهِ العَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made disgrace to befall his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he bound it upon the head of their chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the head of each of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) It is related in a trad. respecting the battle of Bedr, that 'Otbeh the son of Rabee'ah said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirojiEuwA walaA tuqaAtiluwA waA@EoSibuwhaA biraA^osiY","text_ar":"اِرْجِعُوا وَلَا تُقَاتِلُوا وَا@عْصِبُوهَا بِرَاْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Return ye, and fight not; and bind it upon my head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning attach and attribute to me the disgrace that will befall you for relinquishing the battle and inclining to peace. (IAth, TA.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwmuwA bimaA EaSabakumo bihi","text_ar":"قُومُوا بِمَا عَصَبَكُمْ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fulfil ye the obligations with which He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has bound you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which He has imposed upon you and attached to you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by his commands and prohibitions. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grasped the thing with his hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) A poet, cited by IAar, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wakun~aA yaA qurayo$u A_i*aA EaSabonaA\n                      \n                     \n                        yajiYo'u EiSaAbunaA bidamK EabiyTi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we were, O Kureysh, when we grasped"},{"kind":"text","text":"our opponents,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that our grasping brought fresh blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbunaA","text_ar":"عِصَابُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"our grasping"},{"kind":"text","text":"those whom we opposed with the swords. (TA.) ―         -b10-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kept, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlmaA='a","text_ar":"عَصَبَ المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotahu","text_ar":"بَيْتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed, in his house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, not quitting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b11-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went round, encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) It is said in a trad., of the angel Gabriel, on the day of Bedr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado EaSaba raA^osahu AlgubaAru","text_ar":"قَدْ عَصَبَ رَاْسَهُ الغُبَارُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dust had overspread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and clung to, his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado EaSama vaniy~atayohi","text_ar":"قَدْ عَصَمَ ثَنِيَّتَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgubaAru","text_ar":"الغُبَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and if this be not a mistake, the latter verb is syn. with the former:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"being often interchangeable: (L, TA:) the latter phrase means, as also with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dust had stuck to his two central incisors."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESm","text_ar":"عصم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And Ibn Ahmar says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*o EaSaba Aln~aAsa $amaAlN waqurN"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquro","text_ar":"وَقُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqur~N","text_ar":"وَقُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When north wind and cold environ me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlgubaAru biAljabali","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الغُبَارُ بِالجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dust encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, the mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabuwA bihi","text_ar":"عَصَبُوا بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they encompassed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounded, him, looking at him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) and, (Msb, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSibuwA","text_ar":"عَصِبُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. of the former"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and aor. of the latter"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they assembled around him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb. For another explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see 12.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alqawomu biAln~asabi","text_ar":"عَصَبَ القَوْمُ بِالنَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaATuwA bihi","text_ar":"اَحَاطُوا بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, included,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehended, the relations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsmen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~asabu","text_ar":"النَّسَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw Aln~asabi","text_ar":"ذَوُو النَّسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabati AlA_ibilu biAlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَصَبَتِ الاـِبِلُ بِالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels surrounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"encircled, the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alr~iyqu bifiyhi","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الرِّيقُ بِفِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, * TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva became dry in his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyqu faAhu","text_ar":"الرِّيقُ فَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"by its drying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made his mouth dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the saliva adhered to his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Aboo-Mohammad El-Fak'asee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaEoSibu faAhu Alr~iyqu A^aY~a EaSobi\n                      \n                     \n                        EaSoba AljubaAbi bi$afaAhi AlwaTobi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva makes his mouth dry, with what a drying ! as the drying of the spume of camels' milk on the lips of the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba fuwhu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ فُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mouth, with"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2058},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his saliva, became dry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba Alfamu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الفَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwbN","text_ar":"عُصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the latter accord. to the explanation in the K,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirty, from dust and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from vehement thirst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSuwbN","text_ar":"عُصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his bowels were almost dried up with hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is said of the practice of a hungry man's binding round his belly, as expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَعْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba AlA^ufuqu","text_ar":"عَصَبَ الاُفُقُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horizon became red."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O. [In Freytag's Lex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as from the K, in which I do not find it. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) with kesr, (S, O,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHa","text_ar":"فَرِحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of flesh, or flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaba","text_ar":"عَصَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSiba","text_ar":"عَصِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the TA, and so in a verse there cited, not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSabN","text_ar":"عَصَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, firm and compact in flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Other meanings of this verb have been mentioned above.]"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","Mgh","O","TA","Msb","L"]}]}}